added.title: Campfire!
added.description: The Titans put on a show but Robin warns that the performance must be boring or else they'll wake up the wolves.

added.title: What We Learned at Camp
added.description: After not receiving participation medals, the Titans must demonstrate what they learned at camp.

added.title: Girls Night In Part 1
added.description: The Girls Night Out Crew decide to stay in and have a slumber party but an unknown alien threat descends on Jump City.

added.title: The Buddy
added.description: Anais and school psycho Jamie are accused of the same techno-crime. They are forced to team up to discover the real culprit in order to prove their innocence. After solving the case, they realize that they have more in common than they thought...

added.title: The Possession
added.description: Nicole has decided it's time to throw out the family's refrigerator. This doesn't go down too well with Richard, as it's his favorite possession. When it turns out the refrigerator is also a magical storage facility for childhood emotions and memories, it makes sense that Richard is having a hard time letting go.

added.title: The Master
added.description: Dad decides to resolve the Watterson family's differences through the power and magic of his favorite roleplaying game. As they embark on the adventure of a lifetime and battle mythical creatures, will they finally manage to put their differences aside and work together?

added.title: The Silence
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin's conversation dries up, they worry that their friendship is coming to an end. They try to find ways to get the conversation flowing again, but nothing seems to work. Maybe they have just grown apart?

added.title: The Future
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Banana Joe investigate Banana Barbara's mysterious disappearance and uncover an old rival's shadowy scheme in the process.

added.title: Pencil Break Mania
added.description: When Pencil Break Mania hits the Creek, JP finds himself as an unlikely champion and is forced to defend his title against the very best!

added.title: The Last Game of Summer
added.description: It's the last day of summer, and the last chance for Craig to uncover an ancient treasure beneath the Creek.

added.title: Fall Anthology
added.description: In an attempt to finish a school project, Craig remembers some of his favorite Fall moments.

added.title: Free Chili
added.description: When Owen hides a walkie-talkie inside his chili dog, Harold believes it's an alien here to destroy Earth.

added.title: The Date
added.description: When Chef is happy he orders pizza for the kids, this gives Owen & Jude the idea to create a fake secret admirer for Chef.

added.title: Aquarium for a Dream
added.description: Gwen tries to convince Chef to tell the class the truth about their pet goldfish.

added.title: Chata's Quinta Quinceañera
added.description: Vic and Val want to go to a friend's pool party on the same day as their grandma's quinceañera, so they use a magical flute that allows them to teleport and attend both at the same time.

added.title: Legend of the Hidden Skate Park
added.description: While searching for a hidden skate park, V and V happen upon a tribe of wild kids, who live in a society without rules or adults.

added.title: Cleaning Day
added.description: Victor & Valentino gain a newfound respect for cleanliness after Chata's house traps them inside its labyrinth of ancient, magical walls.

added.title: Money Man
added.description: The Bears help Chloe present her project for a college science contest. But Chloe's rival makes things difficult.

added.title: Rescue Ranger
added.description: Tabes helps the Bears rescue Charlie after he gets captured by a villainous game hunter.

added.title: El Oso
added.description: In a flashback to long ago, Charlie has an adventure in the Mexican desert.

added.title: Escandalosos
added.description: The Baby Bears enter a Mexican wrestling tournament.

added.title: Pizza Band
added.description: The Bears get pizza at Papa Bear's Pizza Cave and wind up replacing the place's animatronic band. They're such a hit that they go on tour!

added.title: A New Life
added.description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

added.title: The Perfect Team
added.description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

added.title: Tips
added.description: Apple and Onion have to find a way to ride the Hot Air Balloon which is in their town for one day only.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: The Night Ben Tennyson Came to Town
added.description: Team Tennyson travels to Wheeler, "the liveliest mining town on Route 66", but when Ben becomes paranoid that the Forever Knight is out to get him, he must try to convince his fam while also stopping his new foe from destroying the town.

added.title: And Xingo Was His Name-O
added.description: When a new Xingo app mysteriously appears on Gwen's tablet, Ben can't help himself and activates it despite his cousin's disapproval, springing a trap that transports Ben in the animated world and Xingo back in the real world. It's the ol' switcheroo!

added.title: Fear in the Family
added.description: Ben and Gwen can't wait for the Omni-Copter to arrive at the Great Pyramids, but when bad weather disrupts their flight, they soon come face-to-face with The Fogg and its spawn: The Fogg Family!

added.title: Xingo Nation
added.description: Kevin 11 gives Xingo a power up - setting him loose to wreak havoc on other TV shows - and it is up to Ben to stop them both.

added.title: Heads of the Family
added.description: Team Tennyson stops in at a fringe family reunion, and Ben encounters a whole lot more than kooky cousins namely, Kevin 11 and the Bugg Brothers, whose latest crackpot invention sparks a series of hilarious head-swaps between all parties.

added.title: #BurritoBucket
added.description: Babs loves her job at fast food restaurant Burrito Bucket, but her boss, who's fed up with her chronic lateness and bad case of scatterbrain, would love any excuse to fire her. When a bank robbery breaks out right across the street from work, Babs is torn between her role as a superhero and dutiful Burrito Bucket employee. Will she be able to save the day and keep her job all in the nick of time?

added.title: #Beeline
added.description: When she stumbles across a villainous plot to blow up a bridge, Bumblebee shies from the challenge of taking on the baddies and reaches out to her friends. But when the other heroes are all indisposed, it'll take every ounce of courage Bumblebee has to rise to the occasion … despite being the smallest of the bunch.

added.title: #BeastsInShow
added.description: When Babs and Kara spar over whose dog is better, they decide to settle it at the Metropolis Dog Show, where Ace the Bat-Hound and Krypto the Superdog suddenly find themselves called upon to save the day… in more ways than one.

added.title: #RageCat
added.description: Jessica Cruz is convinced she can find the purr-fect forever home for Dexter, a cat who has been deemed unadoptable because he's basically the worst cat in the world. Her overbearing persistence in trying to get him adopted leads Dexter to become Dex-Starr, an evil Red Lantern supervillain! Can Jess still find the good in a fuzzy little nemesis who is trying to kill her?

added.title: #TheGoodTheBadAndTheBizarre
added.description: Everything is going well for Kara Danvers, both as a teen and a superhero, until she starts taking the blame for things she didn't do, and the emergence of a new supervillain threatens to destroy Supergirl's hard-earned reputation.

added.title: Parallel Paradox
added.description: Elliott finds himself having to be in two places at once.

added.title: Problematic Prophecies
added.description: Elliott and Mo make a new friend, Nara, who has a very special ability.

added.title: The Return
added.description: A new threat arrives in Beach City.

added.title: Jail Break
added.description: Steven teams up with a new ally to rescue the Gems.

added.title: Full Disclosure
added.description: Steven tries to avoid Connie so he doesn't have to tell her about his most recent harrowing adventure.

added.title: Open Book
added.description: Steven and Connie want a new ending to a beloved book series, so Steven takes them into Rose's Room to re-enact it.

added.title: Joy Ride
added.description: The Cool Kids help Steven put some fun back in his life.

added.title: Man Up
added.description: When Buttercup's aggression inadvertently allows villain Man-Boy to escape, she starts a new-age lifestyle in an effort to be more calm. But when Man-Boy returns to enact his revenge, Buttercup must embrace the balance between punching and hugging in order to defeat him.

added.title: Bye Bye, Bellum
added.description: The Mayor becomes dependent on the Powerpuff Girls after his assistant Ms. Bellum departs, leaving the girls so busy they accidentally hire the dangerous Bianca Bikini as his new assistant! When Bianca captures the Powerpuff Girls, the Mayor finds the tables turned and must rely on himself to help them.

added.title: Little Octi Lost
added.description: Buttercup steals Octi to teach Bubbles a lesson but ends up wanting to keep him for herself.

added.title: Strong Armed
added.description: When Bubbles breaks her arm and gets a powerful robotic cast, she must learn to stop being timid and embrace her smashy side to defeat the sleazy, sinister Pack Rat!

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: Orb
added.description: The dreams of Finn, Jake, and BMO fall under the influence of a mysterious orb.

added.title: Abstract
added.description: As Jake goes through some personal changes, he's haunted by a sinister dream encounter with his brother Jermaine.

added.title: Ketchup
added.description: BMO and Marceline swap stories about their recent adventures.

added.title: Fionna and Cake and Fionna
added.description: An unexpected critic shows up at Ice King's latest Fionna and Cake book reading.

added.title: Whispers
added.description: While safeguarding a frightened Sweet P, Finn is led into a confrontation with an old foe.

added.title: The Glitch
added.description: In order to stop Unagami the ninja must obtain three Key-tanas, the first of which is hidden in the game zone Terra Kerana, one of Prime Empire's most dangerous game environments.

added.title: The Cliffs of Hysteria
added.description: While being chased by Unagami's dreaded Red Visors the ninja must climb the 'Cliffs of Hysteria', however, they make a startling discovery: Unagami is converting players into energy cubes in order to build a portal into the real world!

added.title: The Maze of the Red Dragon
added.description: Still in the game zone Terra Kerana, the Samurai guide Okino has to choose between helping his allies the ninja, or obeying the evil orders of his Master, Unagami.

added.title: One Step Forward, Two Steps Back
added.description: When the ninja learn that the only way to acquire the second Key-tana is by winning a dangerous race in Terra Technica they'll have to find some racing cars in unexpected ways.

added.title: Racer Seven
added.description: As the ninja prepare for the brutal Speedway Five-Billion race, Lloyd meets a race driver named Seven, who is programmed to lose, but who may hold the key to victory.

added.title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

added.title: Jeff's New Toy
added.description: Jeff wants to keep his new, flying "Wrath Hover Ginsbot" toy in its box. Clarence is desperate to play with the toy. And poor Sumo is caught in the middle.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Honk
added.description: Seeking to improve his communication skills, Clarence turns to a squeeze horn. It's really annoying.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Maxin' and Relaxin'
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a mix tape from his parents' house.

added.title: Thomas Fights Back
added.description: Thomas Wants to get the park founder's statue back.

added.title: Bachelor Party! Zingo!
added.description: Skips must plan the perfect bachelor party for his cousin, Quips.

added.title: Tent Trouble
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby must replace CJ's expensive tent before she realizes they destroyed it.

added.title: Real Date
added.description: Mordecai and CJ want to go on a romantic date.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Dog Daze/In Focus
added.description: Dog Daze: Lightning discovers a new Bakugan, Artulean, leading to an unhealthy rivalry with Howlkor./In Focus: While Lia's newswoman mom does an expose on the AO Strata the Hunter tries to capture Hydorous.

added.title: The Exit/The Lost and the Cost
added.description: The Exit: The AO compete with a rival Brawling team for ViewTube hits leading to a "winner take all" brawl./The Lost and the Cost: Everett Ray, a promotor, tries to get the AO to join an official league for Bakugan Battling.

added.title: Mr. Moon/What's Wrong with Dan
added.description: Mr. Moon: Wynton finds a new Bakugan who proves difficult to control but things get more complicated when Col. Tripp seizes control of Trox./What's Wrong with Dan: With "Dan" behaving strangely toward the AO Lightning sniffs out the truth- an impostor!

added.title: Babysitting Bedlam/Rubbed the Wrong Way
added.description: Rubbed the Wrong Way: After a Bakugan field errupts the town kids stampede to get their own Bakugan but when the field is contaminated Lia must save the day./Babysitting Bedlam: Dan and Wynton meet a strange boy who leads them into an underground maze where they discover the boy's Bakugan has been enslaved.

added.title: Mask of Power/Story Holes
added.description:
Mask of Power: Philomena Dusk from AAAnimus Corp. hires Magnus and gives him a control implant to bolster the power of his Bakugan to defeat Dan./Story Holes:  
A cryptic call leads the AO in search of a missing Bakugan but they soon realize the call was actually a test from a mysterious benefactor.

added.title: Scary Tales
added.description: During the gang's Halloween party, Unikitty discovers Brick isn't scared of anything! To get him in the holiday spirit, the gang tell their own ideas of what a spooky story is, hoping to scare the emotionless Rick for once, with each tale even scarier (and sillier) than the last!

added.title: Float On
added.description: Unikitty plans a parade to celebrate being unique, with everyone designing their own personalized floats! But Master Frown plans to ruin the parade with a super depressing float! It becomes an intense (and hilariously slow) car-versus-car float duel as Unikitty and the others try and take him down! Will Unikitty pump the brakes on Frown's low-speed scheme?

added.title: Space Mission: Danger
added.description: After their spaceship explodes, Unikitty and the gang float helplessly through space. As they try to formulate a plan that will get them home safe, they flash back to how each of them is responsible for their ship being destroyed. Will they make it home, and more importantly who will be to blame if they don't.

added.title: Top of the Naughty List
added.description: It's Christmas Eve and Brock is excited for Santa to come and visit as he settles down for a bedtime story from Master Frown, Unikitty and gang burst in. They are there to stop Master Frown from ruining any more Christmases. Frown pleads innocent but Unikitty and the gang tell the stories of the past Christmases he has already ruined.  Will Frown prove his innocence or will he rocket to the top of the Naughty List?

added.title: BatKitty
added.description: The gang are at the local laundromat cleaning their clothes, when Unikitty finds Batman's uniform mixed in with her clothes.  Intoxicated by the coolness of it, Unikitty takes on the persona of Batman and begins to fight crime.  When she accidentally causes Master Frown to step up his crime game, she will need the help of her friends, dressed as Robin, to stop him.

added.title: My Dad Can Beat up Your Dad
added.description: When a bully says his dad can beat up KO's mom, KO gladly accepts the challenge on Carol's behalf.

added.title: We've Got Pests
added.description: KO, Rad & Enid have to deal with tiny pests wreaking havoc in the bodega.

added.title: You Are Rad
added.description: When KO forgets his name tag, Rad lets him use his, which results in everyone thinking KO is Rad, including Rad himself.

added.title: Legends of Mr. Gar
added.description: Rad and Enid reminisce about when they started working at the bodega and learned how amazing Mr. Gar really is.

added.title: We Got Hacked
added.description: Dendy helps KO, Enid and Rad stop a glitch that threatens to take over the bodega.

added.title: Mao Mao's Nakey
added.description: When MM loses his clothes while trying to scale the Ruby Pure Heart, he has to get back to Sheriff's HQ by daybreak.

added.title: Lucky Ducky Mug
added.description: When Adorabat and Badgerclops break Mao Mao's favorite mug, he gives them the silent treatment.

added.title: Lonely Kid
added.description: When AD has trouble making friends at school, MM tells her the story of how he made his first real friend —BB.

added.title: Try Hard
added.description: When the Sky Pirates take Mao Mao and Badgerclops hostage, it's up to Adorabat to save the day.

added.title: Scared of Puppets
added.description: Mao Mao is scared of puppets.

added.title: Divided We Stand
added.description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. These multiple Dittos can't agree on anything and drive Gwen crazy. However when the chips are down, these Dittos come together as one fighting force in order to defeat Animo and his army of replicant Stinkflies.

added.title: Don't Drink the Water
added.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

added.title: Big Fat Alien Wedding
added.description: Ben and Gwen accompany Max to a wedding, which doesn't make Ben particularly happy, especially given the fact he has to wear a tux and learn how to dance. During the wedding it's revealed that the bride's parents are aliens while the groom's family are ex-Plumbers. It turns out the bride's parents are out to sabotage the wedding because of a long lasting feud with the Plumbers, and take action by demonstrating their destructive powers and causing deadly havoc. Ben, Max and Gwen enter the fray and not only save the day, but make sure the ceremony goes on as planned.

added.title: T.G.I.S
added.description: The Secret Saturdays come to Bellwood to investigate a rash of chupacabra attacks.

added.title: O Mother, Where Art Thou?
added.description: Ma Vreedle threatens to blow up the sun if Ben and the Plumbers don't find her missing son!

added.title: Mud Is Thicker Than Water
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Cousin Lucy try to find out how Psyphon's thugs are getting Plumber technology.

added.title: The Ultimate Heist
added.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

added.title: For a Few Brains More
added.description: Ben, Rook and Max must stop Ultimate Albedo from absorbing Azmuth's intelligence and taking over the galaxy.

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Babies
added.description: When the President calls in the Uncle Grandpa babies, they have to act quickly and use their special baby powers to defuse a missile.

added.title: Birdman
added.description: When Birdman makes the RV's attic his new home, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to make him leave before they're all driven crazy.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Retires
added.description: Uncle Grandpa discovers a new, unusual occupation.

added.title: Fool Moon
added.description: Strange things start happening when Uncle Grandpa installs a moon roof in the RV.

added.title: La Leyenda del Parque Patinetas
added.description: Mientras buscan un parque de patinaje escondido, V y V se encuentran con una tribu de niños salvajes, que viven en una sociedad sin reglas ni adultos.

added.title: Quintos Quinces
added.description: Victor y Valentino quieren ir a la fiesta en la piscina de un amigo el mismo día que la fiesta de quince años de su abuela, así que usan una flauta mágica que les permite teletransportarse y asistir a ambas al mismo tiempo.

added.title: Dia de limpieza
added.description: Victor y Valentino adquieren un nuevo respeto por la limpieza después de que la casa de Chata los atrapa dentro de su laberinto de paredes antiguas y mágicas.

added.title: La Amiga
added.description: Anaís y Jamie forjan una extraña amistad cuando se las acusa de un crimen que no cometieron.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Posesion
added.description: Richard Watterson parece estar sobrenaturalmente unido a su viejo refrigerador.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Amo
added.description: Los Watterson juegan un juego de rol fantástico para resolver sus diferencias.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Silencio
added.description: ¿Acaso Gumball y Darwin se quedaron sin cosas que decirse el uno al otro?
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Futuro
added.description: La mamá de Banana Joe puede predecir el futuro, pero no puede predecir su propia desaparición.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Fogata de campamento!
added.description: Los Titanes montan un espectáculo, pero Robin les advierte que la actuación debe ser aburrida o despertarán a los lobos.

added.title: Lo que aprendimos en el campamento
added.description: Después de no recibir sus medallas de participación, los Titanes deben demostrar lo que aprendieron en el campamento.

added.title: Noche de chicas Parte 1
added.description: El equipo de la Noche de Chicas decide quedarse en casa y celebrar una pijamada, pero una desconocida amenaza alienígena desciende sobre Jump City.

added.title: La noche que Ben Tennyson vino al pueblo
added.description: El equipo Tennyson viaja a Wheeler, "la ciudad minera más animada de la Ruta 66". Pero cuando Ben se pone paranoico con la idea de que el Caballero por Siempre lo esté persiguiendo, debe tratar de convencer a su familia al mismo tiempo que evita que su nuevo enemigo destruya la ciudad.

added.title: Y Xingo era su Nombre
added.description: Cuando la nueva aplicación Xingo aparece misteriosamente en la tableta de Gwen, Ben no puede evitarlo y la activa a pesar de la desaprobación de su prima. Así, lanza una trampa que transporta a Ben al mundo animado y a Xingo de vuelta al mundo real.

added.title: Miedo en la Familia
added.description: Ben y Gwen están ansiosos por que el Omni-Copter llegue a las Grandes Pirámides. Pero cuando el mal tiempo interrumpe su vuelo, pronto se enfrentan cara a cara con Neblina y sus engendros: iLa familia Niebla!

added.title: Nacion Xingo
added.description: Kevin 11 aumenta la potencia de Xingo -que queda libre y causa estragos en otros programas de televisión-, y Ben es el responsable de detener a los dos.

added.title: Perder la cabeza
added.description: El equipo Tennyson se da una vuelta por una reunión familiar alternativa, y Ben se encuentra con mucho más que primos excéntricos, concretamente con Kevin 11 y los Hermanos Bicho, cuyo último invento alocado desata una serie de intercambios de cabeza divertidísimos entre todos los grupos.

added.title: La Falla
added.description: Para detener a Unagami, los Ninjas debe obtener 3 Keytanas, la primera está escondida en Tierra Karana, uno de los entornos de juego más peligrosos.

added.title: Los Acantilados de la Histeria
added.description: Los Ninjas suben a los Acantilados de la histeria y descubren que Unagami convierte a los jugadores en cubos de energía para construir un portal.

added.title: El Laberinto del Dragon Rojo
added.description: Aún en la zona de juego de Tierra Karana, Okino tiene que elegir entre ayudar a sus aliados ninjas, u obedecer las órdenes de su Maestro, Unagami.

added.title: Un Paso Adelante, Dos Pasos Atras
added.description: La única manera de que los Ninjas obtengan segunda Keytana es ganando una carrera en Tierra Technica y tiene que conseguir autos de carreras para eso.

added.title: Piloto Siete
added.description: Mientras los Ninjas se preparan para la carrera Cinco Billones por Hora, Lloyd conoce a la Piloto Siete quien puede tener la clave de la victoria.

added.title: Una Nueva Vida
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín abandonan sus hogares y se mudan a la ciudad, donde se conocen por primera vez.

added.title: El Equipo Perfecto
added.description: A Cebollín le preocupa que su relación con Manzana corra peligro cuando un gato callejero entra en su vida.

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Segunda parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 2 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Tercera parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 3 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Propinas
added.description: Luego de destruir por accidente el boleto de Falafel para un concierto, Manzana y Cebollín deben descubrir un modo de evitar la furia de Falafel.

added.title: Capullos de Rosa
added.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

added.title: Voleibol
added.description: Steven está decidido a ayudar a la Perla original de Diamante Rosa para sanar la cicatriz en su rostro.

added.title: El Dia Divertido de Falafel
added.description: Cuando Falafel decide empacar sus cosas e ir a la ciudad, Manzana y Cebollín deben convencerlo de quedarse.

added.title: Manzana esta en Problemas
added.description: Bistec con Queso, malhumorado, desafía a Manzana a una pelea. De ese modo, Manzana puede embarcarse con Cebollín en una misión para encontrar el origen del malhumor de Bistec con Queso.

added.title: #LaCubetaDeBurritos
added.description: A Babs le encanta su trabajo en el restaurante de comida rápida "La Cubeta de Burritos" , pero a su jefe, que está harto de que ella siempre llegue tarde y de su enorme dispersión, le encantaría encontrar cualquier excusa para despedirla. Cuando se produce un robo a un banco que está enfrente de su trabajo, Babs no puede decidir si encarnar su papel de superheroína o el de empleada obediente de La Cubeta. Pero ¿será capaz de salvar a todos y conservar su empleo justo a tiempo?
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #Beeline
added.description: Cuando tropieza con un malvado complot para hacer explotar un puente de la ciudad, Bumblebee se espanta y acude a sus amigas para que derroten a los malhechores. Pero cuando todas sus super amigas están ocupadas, Bumblebee debe buscar cada gramo de coraje en ella para hacer frente a la situación, a pesar de ser la más pequeña del grupo.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Mi Papa Puede Vencer a Tu Papa
added.description: Cuando un bravucón dice que su papá puede darle una paliza a la mamá de K.O., nuestro héroe acepta con alegría el desafío en nombre de Carol.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Tu Eres Rad
added.description: Cuando K.O. se olvida su chapa identificatoria, Rad le presta la suya, lo cual hace que todos piensen que K.O. es Rad, incluido el mismo Rad.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Tenemos Plagas
added.description: K.O., Rad y Enid tienen que lidiar con una plaga diminuta y molesta que está desatando el caos en el almacén.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Leyendas del Senor Gar
added.description: Rad y Enid recuerdan la época en la que comenzaron a trabajar en el almacén y entendieron lo fabuloso que es el Sr. Gar.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Ya Nos Hackearon
added.description: Dendy ayuda a K.O., Enid y Rad a arreglar un problema técnico que amenaza con apoderarse de la bodega.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: #ElShowDeLasBestias
added.description: Cuando Babs y Kara discuten sobre cual de sus perros es mejor, deciden resolver la situación en el concurso anual de perros de Metrópolis, donde Ace, el Bati-sabueso y Krypto, el Superperro, deberán salvar el día.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #GatoRabioso
added.description: Jessica Cruz está convencida de que puede conseguirle un hogar definitivo perfecto para Dexter, un gato que la gente considera inadoptable porque, básicamente, es el peor gato del mundo.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #LaBuenaLaMalaYLaBizarra
added.description: Las cosas van bien en la vida de Kara Danvers, como adolescente y como superheroína, hasta que comienza a hacerse responsable de cosas que no hizo y la aparición de un nuevo supervillano amenaza con destruir la reputación que tanto le costó ganar a Supergirl.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: El Desnudo de Mao Mao
added.description: Cuando Mao Mao pierde la ropa mientras intenta escalar el Rubí Puro Corazón, tiene que regresar al cuartel general antes de que amanezca.

added.title: La Taza del Patito de la Suerte
added.description: Cuando Adorabat y Colosal rompen la taza favorita de Mao Mao, el sheriff los castiga con su silencio.

added.title: Chico Solitario
added.description: Cuando a Adorabat le cuesta conocer amigos nuevos en la escuela, Mao Mao le cuenta la historia de cómo conoció a su primer amigo real...Bao Bao.

added.title: Esforzarse Mas
added.description: Cuando los Piratas del Cielo se llevan a Mao Mao y a Colosal, depende de Adorabat salvarlos a ambos.

added.title: Miedo a los Titeres
added.description: Mao Mao le teme a los títeres.

added.title: Historias de miedo
added.description: Durante la fiesta de Halloween de la banda, iUnikitty descubre que Rick no le teme a nada! Para contagiarle el espíritu festivo, Unikitty cuenta sus propias ideas de lo que es una historia espeluznante, con la esperanza de asustar al inconmovible de Rick por una vez. iPero cada cuento es aún más espeluznante (y más tonto) que el anterior!

added.title: El Desfile
added.description: Unikitty planea un desfile para celebrar lo que cada uno tiene de único, idonde cada uno diseñará sus propias carrozas personalizadas! Pero Master Frown planea arruinar el desfile con una carroza súper deprimente. El desfile se convierte en un duelo intenso (y de una lentitud divertidísima) de coche contra carroza mientras Unikitty y los demás intentan derribar a Master Frown! ¿Le pondrá un freno Unikitty al complot a baja velocidad de Frown?

added.title: Mision Espacial Peligrosa
added.description: Después de la explosión de su nave espacial, Unikitty y la banda flotan indefensos por el espacio. Mientras tratan de formular un plan que los lleve a casa a salvo, vuelven a ver qué parte de la responsabilidad por la destrucción de su nave tiene cada uno. ¿Lograrán volver a casa? Y lo que es más importante, ¿quién tendrá la culpa si no lo hacen?

added.title: Lista de Traviesos
added.description: Es Nochebuena y Brock está emocionado por la visita de Santa Claus. Mientras se prepara para que Master Frown le lea un cuento para dormir, Unikitty y la banda irrumpen en su casa. Están ahí para evitar que Master Frown arruine más Navidades. Frown se declara inocente, pero Unikitty y la banda cuentan las historias de las Navidades pasadas que ya arruinó. ¿Frown probará su inocencia o se pondrá a la cabeza de la lista de los traviesos?

added.title: Bati-Kitty
added.description: La banda está lavando ropa en la lavandería local, cuando Unikitty encuentra el uniforme de Batman mezclado con su ropa. Embriagada al ver lo genial que es el disfraz, Unikitty adopta la personalidad de Batman y comienza a luchar contra el crimen. Cuando accidentalmente hace que Master Frown intensifique su actividad delictiva, Unikitty necesitará la ayuda de sus amigos, vestidos todos como Robin, para detenerlo.

added.title: Bajo los Reflectores
added.description: Cuando la reportera Verónica Venegas, madre de Lia, hace un reportaje acerca de Los Fantásticos, Strata El Cazador intenta capturar a Hydorous.

added.title: Enredos Perrunos
added.description: Lightning descubre un nuevo Bakugan, Artulean, y eso desata una fuerte rivalidad entre él y Howlkor.

added.title: Tutores Bakugan
added.description: Dan y Wynton conocen a un extraño chico que los lleva a un laberinto subterráneo, donde descubren que el Bakugan del chico ha sido esclavizado.

added.title: El Equipo Exit
added.description: Los Fantásticos compiten por el número de visitas en sus videos con un equipo rival llamado "El equipo Exit" en una batalla donde se juegan el todo por el todo.

added.title: Una Necesidad Inquietante
added.description: La aparición de un nuevo campo Bakugan hace que los chicos del pueblo corran a buscar a sus propios Bakugan. Pero cuando el campo es contaminado, Lia debe salvarlos a todos.

added.title: Sr. Luna
added.description: Wynton encuentra un nuevo Bakugan que resulta difícil de controlar, y las cosas se complican cuando el Coronel Tripp se apodera de Trox.

added.title: Perdidas y Ganancias
added.description: Un promotor llamado Everett Ray quiere convencer a Los Fantásticos de ingresar a una liga oficial de Batallas Bakugan.

added.title: Que Ocurre con Dan
added.description: Cuando Dan se comporta de forma extraña con los Fantásticos, Lightning olfatea la verdad: iUn impostor!

added.title: Una Verdad a Medias
added.description: Un críptico correo electrónico lleva a Los Fantásticos en busca de un Bakugan desaparecido, pero pronto se dan cuenta de que el correo era una prueba de un misterioso benefactor.

added.title: Mascara de Poder
